parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience various electrical issues, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the cooling fan can cause the vehicle to overheat, which can lead to engine damage and potentially cause accidents.
The failure of the clutch system can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and vehicle unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door latch can cause the door to jam, which can lead to injury or death in the event of a crash or fire.
symptoms: unable to open door from inside or outside

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear coupler can cause the vehicle to vibrate and bind, which can lead to loss of control and accidents.
The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, which can lead to accidents.
The failure of the 120V outlet can cause medical equipment to malfunction, which can lead to health risks.
symptoms: unable to provide power as promised

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or fail to accelerate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission gives out while on the highway

causing the vehicle to not start or drive; the transmission would not shift gears at 4000 RPMs unless the driver lets off the gas and then gives it gas again; the transmission slips out of gear while driving; the transmission makes a grinding noise when shifting gears; the vehicle loses all ability to accelerate and starts decelerating on upward climbs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor can lead to the airbag not operating as needed in the event of a crash, putting the occupants' safety at risk.
symptoms: The airbag sensor on the passenger's side of the vehicle fails to determine and classify the weight of the passenger seated in the seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ESC system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The ESC light comes on while driving; the vehicle fails to respond to driver input

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brakes fail to stop the vehicle
causing it to slide down a carriageway and hit a parked vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine sludge can cause premature engine failure, leading to sudden loss of power, stalling, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Unintended acceleration and hesitation can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Hesitation when depressing the accelerator pedal

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine coil failure can cause loss of power, stalling, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Unexplained acceleration can cause the vehicle to suddenly speed up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without input from the driver
the vehicle continues to accelerate even when the brake pedal is pressed
and the vehicle accelerates even when the accelerator pedal is not pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission malfunction can cause the vehicle to surge or accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle surges or accelerates unexpectedly when starting from a complete stop
the vehicle surges or accelerates unexpectedly when shifting into reverse
and the vehicle fails to accelerate when needed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine shut-down can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine shuts down without warning
the vehicle loses power and stalls
and the vehicle's ABS sensor malfunctions
causing the vehicle to go into "fail-safe" mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Adaptive cruise control malfunction can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The adaptive cruise control accelerates the vehicle without input from the driver
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly when using adaptive cruise control
and the vehicle fails to respond to input from the driver when using adaptive cruise control.
